tip.text: Did the chefs choice nigiri and 3 pieces in I could tell this was not the sushi it claimed to be. The omakase should be the best sushi in the house but I was disappointed with this chefs choice.
Such a great crew! Very knowledgeable about the area and some of the nicest (and funniest) people you can meet. Lucky if you get Capt. Levi, Dave and Joe on your boat. Go during whale season FTW.
Not only one on London's best breakfasts (Ox Cheek Benedict and  the Cocotte are both must haves!), but the staff is abso amazing! Consider yourself lucky if you get Andre (one of London's best).
Brunch and service were top notch (Chorizo and eggs and French toast)! They used to have the perfect Mexican michelada (i.e. no tom juice but spicy lemonade) but no longer make it!! Why PT!? Why?!?
An amazing space (upstairs and down) with great food including what is easily  one of London's best burgers.

formattedAddress: 89 Marylebone High St (btw Paddington and Moxon Sts)

tip.text: No idea why this isn't place rated a 9.0 at least. Simply the best nigiri I've had in London. Chef Lin and the staff have the best kept secret in Camden. Go omakasi and don't look back.
Not only an outstanding bourbon selection  (4 roses small batch) but quite possibly the best Zombie I've ever had in London.
I so wanted to like this place but alas it was not to be. Had the cold seafood platter (meh) and the half grilled lobster (overcooked). Kitchen was slow and food was expensive for what you got.
Ok space but every ounce of alcohol gets measured. Crowded at HH bc of the 2 for 1 deals. Stay away from punches which are light on alcohol and heavy on the juice.

At this caliber, I hesitate to even call it German food. Great experience overall. Food was delicious, service was ok (our waitress was a little inexperienced, kept checking in every literally 5 mins)
Why is this place not rated higher?? Great service and really good seafood. Easily one of the top 5 restaurants in St. Julian/Marina. Follow your servers reco and by all means, save room for desert.
Amazing venue in a converted house with delicious food and an attentive waitstaff. Highly reco the seafood soup, foie gras and any fish special they have that day. Great selection of local wine, too.

Big hotel, nice staff. But Westin, here's a tip: You wonder why no one goes into your pool (or hot tubs)? It's bc it's freezing even when it's 21c out. The rates you charge should afford a little heat
Great brunch place. Reco the chicken and waffles and the eggs bene  (also conveniently served on waffles). Stay clear of the michelada (damn near awful) but everything else makes it worth going.
Great way to spend the day with some retail therapy and tons of food options.
Friendly, knowledgeable staff will make any drink you want, well.  Maybe not the best cocktails on the planet but you'd be amiss not to be here.. Start with the Killer Zombie.go from there. Big menu.
It is not normal for food to taste this good. Never a bad dish.
Not bad food. Good drinks. And ok service. Good locale in a neighborhood w lots of options.

formattedAddress: R. Padre João Manuel, 1115 (R. Barão de Capanema)

tip.text: Limited brunch menu. Hash was just ok but the service was great and they have bottomless bloodies, mimosas and hix fizzes that you can mix and match on!
Why isn't this place more packed??? Had a lot on the menu (so reasonably priced) and have yet to have anything bad. They have single-handedly renewed my interest in lobster rolls so don't miss that.
Lovely Peruvian place w/a great staff. Things to try: The salmon, marinated steak, beet salad, chicken, and of course the ceviche. The tuna tartar was just ok (bit flavorless). Save room for desert!
Nice little, unassuming neighborhood gem. Eggs and meat was ok but the eggs and salmon and French toast were delish.
Voted best international hotel bar and for good reason. Every drink is immaculately prepared, delicious and not served, but outrightly presented by an attentive staff. Menu changes often.
Great facility with pretty much everything you'd need (except an atm for some reason). Friendly staff who are always at your beck and call.
Better than the rating portrays (6.7 at the time). Linguine and crab was great as well as the sea breem (pic). And by all means save some room for desert to share. Choco cheesecake was good.

The food was indeed delicious and creative, but it was the outstanding and attentive service that made this such an anazing meal. Reco the beet salad, pork loin, and just about any desert on the menu.
You have to love a bartender that knows how to make a good drink...and every bartender at Berners can do this. Come for the drinks, stay for the scenery.
Renovated and upgraded the food for a fantastic all around experience.

venue.name: 麗尊酒店 Royal Lees Hotel Kaohsiung

tip.text: I honestly could not get enough of this food. Service was also outstanding. Order ahead and get the 1/2 or while duck and the chef will prepare/serve it 2 or 3 way, respectively.
Taipei's first true speakeasy and you can't go wrong. Everything is 'off menu' so sit back, pick your spirit and drink in the magic.
Great, quick and reasonably priced seafood. Crab (chili or peppered, your pick) and salted egg shrimp are a must. Duck and mango salad is good as well.

venue.name: Jumbo Seafood Gallery 珍宝海鮮樓

tip.text: More interested in how they got there and they built them rather than the actual structure itself, which is frankly a little underwhelming.
Good but busy brunch place.
You'd be hard pressed to find a better cocktail in Bath. Lots of nooks and crannies w/the Champaign Lounge/Terrace. Look for Clem and you'll find the best Old Fashion you ever had (make it a triple).
Great find and one of my fav burgers in London. If you're up for the unusual (and they have it on the menu) bypass the usual fare and go straight to the Social Experiment Burger (varies by week).
If you try here and Cake and Brunch you've completed your list of best brunch places in Barca. Picnic actually also has great bloodies which may give it a leg up over C&B.
It may not look like it at first, but you're in for a treat. Old fashioneds are deelish, but try an Acapulco (fantastic drink). If you're nice to Marco maybe he'll let you sip his secret bloody mix.
Very nice hotel. All the luxury of the W without the clubbing. Good central locale.
Finally get to try my first one. A good burger (greasy, great for hangovers) but think 5 guys is better.
Great non-korean bbq find! Most of the food is good but you'd be a fool to miss the chicken (whole or otherwise) and pork belly tacos.
Need help the wait list times (double whatever they say inside an hour) but def worth the wait. Both the benedict w/waffles and the mushroom scramble were perfect.

formattedAddress: C. Enric Granados, 19 (C. Consell de Cent)

tip.text: May be a wait but take advantage of the shared table in back (be prepared to speak up tho as they tend to easily forget you). Skillet was great (better if it was a scramble) and pancakes were perfect!

The chef is def creative, the service was fantastic and those drinks! The food unfort just missed being great tho. A little over cooked here, a little lack of flavor there. May come back to try again.
The name doesn't quite capture the the great food. Eggs a little overcooked on the Benedict but still quite tasty. Duck confit w egg was deliciously flavorful. Save room for a glazed donut!
Think the menu changes often. Great start with the salad, but octopus was tough and pork belly was just ok. Scallops were good. Luckily they have a strong cocktail program and a great staff.
Cocktail program may need help (stay away from the Bloody) but their Sunday playlist makes it easy to hang out for a bit. Grab a pint of Landlord and stay awhile.
Service was lackadaisical. Bloody Mary was mediocre. Eggs Benny was good (really well prepared) but not enough to make up for the shortfalls.
Food is delish, cocktail program looks delish but is actually just ok.
Holy schnizzle, must get the duck liver mousse. You've never had anything like it before. Not PB&J, PD&J (Popcorn, Duck & Jam). Trust.
On a nice day: Go!
Hit and miss cocktails but the staff are nice. It's tradition for us on new years day.
Great views but the kitchen went a notch down over the last couple years. Oysters ok (not the freshest). Blt w/avo just ok too.
Def leave room for desert. There's a wide range and omg is it amazing.
So far, easily the best sushi in London. Splurge a little and grab the omakase.
One of the most complicated menu/ordering processes of all time. But once past that, you're in for surely one of London's best meals. Tiger prawn soup, salmon starter and cod were all near perfect
One of the oldest recipes and crafted with care: The Rum Old Fashioned.
Outstanding cocktail program. If you're confident in your masculinity (and your drinking) and ok w/pink start w/Barons Tipple with overproof rum. Holy schnizzle!
Egg and Avo was good. Bacon was cold but somehow still delicious. Start with the bloody mary!
Now that's a proper and delicious bloody mary!
Has to be some of seafood in Stockholm. Cod and cockles were especially amazing, perfectly cooked (only complaint which is small was the day e was heavily salted). Great take on a bloody Mary, too!
Here's a start up, there's a start up.
Def one of the best brunch places in London. Eggs Hussard was great. The pancakes look and taste awesome. And it's flat down the best Bloody Mary I've had in London so far.
Ok so started out a little slow/low w/the tiny drink but these guys def know how to cook. Crispy fish skin to start (pic) and cod as a main which was cooked perfectly. Service was good as well.
I think it's supposed to be a drink. Looks like the kids version. Are they serving drinks to kids now!?!?? New Old Fashion. Taste: meh.
Service was very friendly at the new place. Burgers were ok. Cooked exactly as ordered but the 'lava' grill runs a bit hot so you get some crispy black char with each bit (meh). Loved the fries!
Packed so be prepared for a leisurely stroll. Go off hours for less queues
Avoid the line for 'the bird's and go straight to the line for bar and restaurants for the whole experience.
Solid Italian. Fish was cooked perfectly. I had the seafood spaghetti which was delicious.

Holy schnizzle. It really is the whole package. Great food. Outstanding drinks, and, oh yeah, there's a view. Pate, ceviche and mac&cheese are all outstanding! Thanks to Aaron for a great bar program!
Craft cocktails at their finest. Go have fun with anything on or off the menu. You won't be disappointed.
The fantastic service may distract from the amazing food. Prepare to be treated. Think less and try the tasting menu.
Holy cow that's a great drink. And the presentation on (literally) every drink is worth just ordering it. Have fun w the menu. I assure, it won't disappoint.
Served like a piece of cake, the kimchee is actually pretty good. Bowls didn't have much flavor but the marinated pork was delicious.
Eggs Benedict w/spinach and a very good, albeit short, bloody Mary. Good flavor on both and eggs were cooked perfectly. Good service, too!
The Sazerac Scarves style.
Nothing like finding a great craft cocktail bar. Plenty of great house drinks but don't be afraid to try the old standards.
It's supposed to be fresh so if that's the best you can say...Okasame was clearly pre-made as it took all of 2 mins to come out...w no explanation of what was what. Service was virtually nonexistent.
Start here. Service: outstanding.  Squid: yes! Fried chicken: Best. 3 Tom salad: deelish. And for God sakes, dont forget to indulge in a cocktail or two.
Oysterville!.
Menu changes often but cured meats are evergreen and delicious.  Drinks are fun and inventive.  Feel free to have fun with it all!
Whatever you do for brunch, wrap it up with a single serving of french toast.
Friendly service in this hole-in-the-wall place. Burgers are cooked perfectly but theres not much to them in regards to condiments (i.e.- kinda plain). Also, fries (chips) are  closer to crisps.

venue.name: Boys and Girls Club of America

formattedAddress: 1 Carlton B Goodlett Pl (btwn Grove & McAllister St)

tip.text: Said complex negroni...complete with 3 different tastings.
Athens mixology specializing in rum drinks!
Horrible view. Just...just aweful.
Best marg I've had in the islands! Get them on the rocks. Nice family owned restaurant with a friendly staff.
Gorgeous lobby, great views.
Salmon tartar and sardines are great.
Cool new menu. Great new drinks.  Just flip and pick. Can't go wrong with any of them...and even if you do you're still drinking. Cheers!
